# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Internal vs public boundary
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Loose session-planning files (task_plan, findings, progress, reviews)
# generated during development MUST NOT be tracked at the repo root. The
# patterns below catch the common drift cases. Operators should commit
# durable docs to docs/ instead of dropping them at root.
#
#
#
# These ignores apply ONLY at the repo root (note the leading slash).
#
#
/task_plan.md
/findings.md
/progress.md
/review.md
/review_comment.md
/review_comment_pr*.md
/review_pr*.md
/RELEASE_NOTES_*.md
/EXEC-SUMMARY-*.md
/pr-review-*.md
/pr*_review.md
# Loose PR-body drafts at repo root — keep them out of public sources.
# The leading dot catches hidden-file variants too.
/.pr-body*.md
/pr-body*.md
/pr_body*.md

# Public worktree / sync staging (created by release/scripts/sync_public.*).
# This is a generated mirror of the sanitized public tree; do not check it in.
public-stage/
release/.cache/
